<h3>What types of materials should <em>not</em> be submitted to ScholarSphere?</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Sensitive data, including but not limited to personally indentifiable information (PII), as covered by FERPA and HIPAA, specific locations of endangered plants and animals, or protected archeological sites.  If you are unsure, we can help you determine if the data are appropriate for deposit.</li>
  <li>Any content for which you do not own the intellectual property rights or do not have permission from the copyright holder. </li>
</ul>

<h3>What if I don’t own the copyright to something I want to deposit?  Can I still upload it? </h3>
<p>
If you do not own the copyright yourself, you must receive permission from the rights holder before depositing that material. ScholarSphere is not responsible for obtaining copyright permissions for contributors.
</p>

